Diagnosis (revised after
Jiang et al ., 2019
). Rostrum moderately elongate, gradually constricted from head, extending to the 5 th antennomere. Gnathochilarium formed by incompletely fused sclerites. Two pairs of tiny macrosetae on anterior part of gnathochilarium. Anterior margin of collum deeply concave. Body setation sparse and short. Prozonites with flat tubercles, metazonites without tubercles. Anterior and posterior gonopods with six podomeres; 6 th podomere of anterior gonopods short, spoon-shaped with prominent apical projection; 6 th podomere of posterior gonopods with stout cone-shaped base and extremely elongate extension, without spines or notches.

The last pair of pleurites large, closely in touch with each other (
Fig. 1G
). Detailed structures of telson not visible in our male specimens.
